createCommitment(bytes32,address,uint256.details: Removes the commitment from the `commitments` mapping.

params.expiryBlock: The block when a commitment can no longer be claimed.
params.receiver: The address to where the funds must be transfered when claimed.
params.secretHashed: The hash of the secret string.

returns.success: Whether the commitment had been successfully deleted.*

deleteCommitment(bytes32).details: Removes the commitment from the `commitments` mapping.

params.secretHashed: The hash of the secret string.

returns.success: Whether the commitment had been successfully deleted.*

isCommitment(bytes32).details: Checks if a commitment exists in the `commitments` mapping.

params.secretHashed: The hash of the secret string.

submitSecret(bytes,bytes32).details: Checks if the hash of the secret matches the claimed hash. If that is the  case, moves the funds in the commitment from the contract to the receiver address. Changes the `alreadyClaimed` field to `true`.

params.claimedHash: The hash of the commitment that the caller is trying to claim.*
params.secret: The secret string known to the entity who requested the commitment.

withdrawToBridge(bytes32).details: Checks if the commitment has expired. If that is the case, returns the funds in the commitment from the contract back to the bridge. Deletes the commitment.

params.secretHashed: The hash of the secret string.*
